<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Two Guards Die in Calif. Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COMPTON, Calif. (AP) -- Two armed security guards were shot to  
death and two others were critically wounded Sunday after 
apparently arguing with a man at the apartment complex where they 
worked. 
</P>
<P>
	The guards were inside or standing near a guard shack at the New  
Wilmington Arms complex when they were shot shortly before 5:30 
a.m., police Lt. Danny Sneed said. 
</P>
<P>
	There were no immediate arrests. Sneed said the shooter appeared  
to be a man who ``frequents the building'' but it wasn't clear if 
he was a resident. 
</P>
<P>
	All four guards worked for a Torrance company called  
International Total Services. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear whether they fired back at their attacker, as the  
area has no security cameras. No weapon was recovered. 
</P>
<P>
	Compton, about 20 miles south of downtown Los Angeles, has been  
plagued by gang and drug-related violence. But residents of the 
Wilmington Arms said that until the shooting they felt safe inside 
the block-long, two-story complex with its neat stucco apartments 
and trim lawns. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is evil and this is hate. I do feel frightened. I feel  
like we are targets,'' said Shirley Thompson, who has lived in the 
complex for more than 20 years. 
</P>
<P>
	The dead guards were identified as Remigio Molinao, 49, and  
Rodrico Paz, 62. 
</P>
<P>
	Saul Conner Martinez, 59, and Rodolso Bombarda, 52, were listed  
in critical condition at Martin Luther King Jr.-Drew Medical 
Center. 


</P>
</TEXT>
