<HEADLINE> Two Guards Die in Calif. Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COMPTON, Calif. (AP) -- Two armed security guards were shot to  
death and two others critically wounded Sunday at an apartment 
complex, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The guards were inside or standing near a guard shack at the  
Wilmington Arms complex when they were shot shortly before 5:30 
a.m. by at least one gunman, police Lt. Danny Sneed said. 
</P>
<P>
	No arrests were made and the identities of the victims were not  
immediately released. 
</P>
<P>
	One guard died at the scene and the other at Martin Luther King  
Jr.-Drew Medical Center, where two others underwent surgery and 
were listed in critical condition, Sneed said. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear whether the guards fired back at their attacker,  
he said. 
</P>
<P>
	A man who had argued with the guards earlier may have shot them,  
although it was unclear how many attackers were involved, police 
said. The area lacked security cameras and no weapon was recovered. 
</P>
<P>
	Compton is about 20 miles south of downtown Los Angeles.  
</P>
</TEXT>
