	It's all history to Tobin, who says he doesn't care about the  
past. 
</P>
<P>
	But Tobin doesn't mind discussing his two years as defensive  
coordinator at Indianapolis and the similarities between the Colts 
and Cardinals -- unpopular owners, fan apathy and players who felt 
they were destined to lose. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1995, the year before Tobin left for the Cardinals, the Colts  
