<HEADLINE> Weather Forces Sports Postponements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Heavy snow and ice forced the postponement of several sports  
events Sunday, including No. 3 Cincinnati's home game against 
Marquette. 
</P>
<P>
	The game was rescheduled for Monday night.  
</P>
<P>
	The game between No. 16 Minnesota at No. 11 Purdue was postponed  
for the second straight day. It was not immediately rescheduled. 
</P>
<P>
	``It could very well be several weeks down the road before we  
can reschedule,'' Purdue spokesman Jim Vruggink said. 
</P>
<P>
	Heavy snow and ice stranded the Golden Gophers in Indianapolis,  
where they practiced Saturday and Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The team was scheduled to leave Monday on a Northwest Airlines  
flight, but university officials were trying to arrange a Sunday 
charter flight. Winter quarter classes start Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Purdue's women's team, ranked No. 3, also had its game at Ohio  
State postponed. No makeup date was set. 
</P>
<P>
	Minor-league hockey games postponed were Columbus at Dayton and  
Johnstown at Huntington in the ECHL and Grand Rapids at Chicago in 
the IHL. 
</P>
<P>
	New York's Aqueduct and Kentucky's Turfway Park also canceled  
Sunday's racing cards. 
</P>
<P>
	A winter storm also forced postponement of several events  
Saturday. 

