<HEADLINE> Springer Bouncer Is Chicago Cop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Jerry Springer's onstage bouncer, Steve Wilkos,  
is a moonlighting Chicago cop who can forget about becoming the 
next Serpico. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm never going anywhere on the police department  
undercover,'' because he's so widely recognized, Wilkos says in 
Sunday's New York Post. 
</P>
<P>
	His shaved head and imposing size (6-foot-3, 225 pounds) add to  
Wilkos' prominence on the Springer show, where he is the first to 
jump in and break up the frequent scuffles between combative 
guests. Being well known for quelling trouble isn't all bad for his 
regular job though. 
</P>
<P>
	``It helps being a little bit of a celebrity, because it calms  
situations down,'' Wilkos said. 
</P>
