<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kings' Murray Out 8-10 Weeks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Right wing Glen Murray, second in  
goals, assists and points for the Los Angeles Kings, is expected to 
miss 8-10 weeks after tearing a ligament in his right knee. 
</P>
<P>
	Murray left the ice on a stretcher with 7:12 remaining in the  
first period of Saturday night's 4-2 victory over Colorado with a 
severely sprained right knee. He was taken to Centinela Hospital 
Medical Center for X-rays, which were negative, and an MRI exam, 
which revealed the sprain and damage to his medial collateral 
ligament. 
</P>
<P>
	Left wing Steve McKenna will undergo abdominal surgery Monday at  
Centinela Hospital. He's expected to miss 10-12 weeks, the team 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	McKenna has missed 24 of the past 25 games because of the  
abdominal strain. He was injured Nov. 5 and returned to the lineup 
after missing 14 games. He aggravated the injury Dec. 9 and has 
missed the past 10 games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
