<HEADLINE> Spurrier Jr. Joins Sooners Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NORMAN, Okla. (AP) -- Oklahoma head coach Bob Stoops hired Steve  
Spurrier Jr. as an assistant Sunday, rounding out his staff. 
</P>
<P>
	Spurrier, son of University of Florida coach Steve Spurrier, was  
hired away from his father's staff. Stoops, who was Florida's 
defensive coordinator when he was hired by Oklahoma to replace John 
Blake, said the younger Spurrier has developed into a solid coach. 
</P>
<P>
	``Over the past few years he has developed outstanding  
communication skills and the ability to recruit tremendous 
student-athletes,'' Stoops said. ``Our players and program will 
really benefit from his knowledge and enthusiasm.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Spurrier, 28, played receiver at Duke University, graduating in  
1994 and beginning his career as a graduate assistant at Florida 
that year. He became a full-time member of his father's coaching 
staff three years later. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, he helped coach receivers and served as special  
teams coach for the Gators. 
</P>
